{
  "$version": 1,
  "title": "PlatformLanguage catalogue seed",
  "description": "Seeded by `localization:seed-platform-languages`. UPSERT keyed on the composite triple `(geography_language_id, geography_country_id, script_code)`. Each row identifies its geography rows by NATURAL keys (`geography_language_code` \u2192 `geography::Language.code`, optional `geography_country_iso2` \u2192 `geography::Country.iso2`) so the seed file stays portable across environments where the vendor auto-increment ids differ. Prefer BCP 47 tags over raw ISO-639-1 for regional variants (fr vs fr-CA, zh-Hans vs zh-Hant). The seeder resolves natural keys \u2192 FK ids at insert time; a lookup miss (missing geography row) aborts the seed and points to `php artisan world:install`.",
  "columns_note": "Fields on each row: `bcp47_code`, `geography_language_code` (natural key), optional `geography_country_iso2` (natural key; only for regional variants), optional `script_code` (ISO 15924; required when the language has multiple written scripts, e.g. zh-Hans / zh-Hant / sr-Latn / sr-Cyrl), `is_active_on_platform`, `is_beta`, `is_system`, `sort_order`. All display fields (name, native_name, direction, flag_emoji) are READ at runtime via accessors chaining through the joined geography rows \u2014 not stored in this file, not stored in platform_languages.",
